2.what is Container Network Interface ? (Assigning an IP address to a container, Every container/pod needs its own network interface and IP.
CNI handles:IP allocation & Interface creation)

3.what is CSI driver? (A CSI Driver (Container Storage Interface Driver) is a standard plugin that allows Kubernetes (and other container orchestration systems) 
to connect to external storage systems such as: AWS EBS , NFS etc)

4.Static volume provisioning and dynamic volume provisioning. Explain in with use case. (the admin manually create the PersistentVolume (PV) before a workload uses it.
USE Case (Pre-existing NFS, iSCSI, SAN storage, Migration from legacy systems, When storage must be manually controlled)

Dynamic volume provisioning -( We create only a PersistentVolume Claim (PVC).
Use Cases :Cloud storage (AWS EBS, GCP PD, Azure Disk), Highly scalable workloads, On-demand volumes

5.what is auto volume expansion. (Auto Volume Expansion = Automatically grow your storage when PVC size increases.
It is a Kubernetes feature that allows a PersistentVolumeClaim (PVC) to automatically increase its storage size without recreating the PVC or restarting the Pod.)

what is land job activity in migration ? (A scheduled activity that loads (or lands) data from the source system into a temporary/staging layer in the target environment.)

