9.pick one requirement and u deployed end to end by using azure services ?
Requirement: (“Deploy a web application with a backend database, make it scalable, and ensure CI/CD automation.”)

1️⃣ Code Repository & CI/CD
Service: Aws DevOps / GitHub
Usage: Store source code, manage branches
Pipeline:
Build Pipeline: Compile code, run unit tests, create Docker image
Release Pipeline: Deploy Docker image to Azure Kubernetes Service

2️⃣ Containerization
Service: Docker + Azure Container Registry (ACR)
Usage:
Build Docker image of the web app
Push image to ACR for secure storage

3️⃣ Orchestration / Compute
Service: Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS)
Usage:
Deploy frontend and backend as pods
Use Deployments and ReplicaSets for scalability
Manage container networking

4️⃣ Database
Service: Azure SQL Database (or Cosmos DB for NoSQL)
Usage:
Managed database with high availability
Connect backend services via environment variables / secrets

5️⃣ Networking & Security
Services:
Azure Load Balancer or Application Gateway for web traffic
Azure Virtual Network (VNet) for secure internal communication
Azure Key Vault for storing secrets and connection strings

6️⃣ Monitoring & Logging
Services:
Azure Monitor & Log Analytics → monitor pods, DB, and app health
Application Insights → track web app performance and errors

7️⃣ Auto-scaling
Service: AKS Cluster Autoscaler + Horizontal Pod Autoscaler
Usage:
Scale pods automatically based on CPU/memory usage
Scale nodes in AKS dynamically

8️⃣ CI/CD Trigger
On every code commit:
Build Docker image → push to ACR
Release pipeline deploys new image to AKS
Automated tests run on QA/UAT environment before production


