23.Any known issues u encountered any pipeline is integrated/ any production code is ur pushing or production any known issue and tell which is critical and how u got resolved 
1️⃣ Issue Encountered
During production deployment, one of the services failed to start after the new container image was deployed.
Error observed: CrashLoopBackOff in Kubernetes pods.
Logs showed missing environment variables and database connection timeout.
Impact: Service downtime, affected 10% of production traffic, critical for user-facing functionality.

2️⃣ Analysis & Root Cause
Root cause analysis included:
Reviewing Kubernetes pod logs and events
Checking pipeline logs and deployment scripts
Validating ConfigMaps and Secrets
Found that:
A new environment variable required by the service was missing in production ConfigMap.
Deployment pipeline did not validate presence of required secrets/configs before pushing.

3️⃣ Resolution

Immediate Fix:
Added the missing environment variable in production ConfigMap
Redeployed the pods → service came up successfully
Preventive Measures:
Updated the CI/CD pipeline to validate required environment variables and secrets before deployment
Added pre-deployment integration tests in a staging environment to catch such configuration issues
Implemented alerting on pod CrashLoopBackOff via Azure Monitor / Prometheus so any future failures trigger immediate notifications

